Mission statement: Our think tank mission is to improve  waste management in Rwanda by employing waste-to-energy practices in order to reduce waste.

Problem statement: Every day, thousands of households and businesses in Kigali miss out on income from compost sales by not sorting their waste due to a lack of awareness. According to the Global Green Growth Institute, organic waste makes up 70% of incoming waste at Nduba Landfill. Organic waste is not sorted at the source and this leads to higher costs for Rwanda's waste management system. We aim to reduce this organic waste from 70% to 60% by 2036 by incentivizing households and businesses to sort compostable waste - connecting them to farmers and agricultural firms who will pay for it. 

Solution statement: We provide an end-to-end source-segregation ecosystem using a color-coded framework to separate organic and inorganic waste at the source. Households receive two distinct colors of locally manufactured, 100% compostable waste bags—Green for organic and Blue for inorganic—which residents use indoors before transferring them to centralized community collection points. For high-volume commercial clients, we deploy heavy-duty, divided multi-bin systems tailored to scale with daily business waste generation. Operation will begin upon securing a government business permit and a manufacturing license from the Rwanda Environment Management Authority (REMA), with initial capital raised through green enterprise grants and public-private partnerships. Prior to a full market launch, we will execute a 3-month pilot program across selected households and businesses to optimize collection logistics and measure segregation compliance. Our unique selling point is delivering Rwanda's first fully compliant, color-coded source-segregation system that utilizes certified biodegradable containment materials, guaranteeing that our bags leave zero plastic footprint during organic composting and recycling processes.

Prototype description: Compostable waste bags and multi-bin systems

